why this exist
==============

nest was expensive in human attention. people needed a machine, we needed
another evening. that number is why nest is suspended and why this repo
exists.

git is the identity provider. not authentik "for now" — for everything git
can actually cover. you open a pr that adds user-vms/you.nix, someone
reviews it, merge hits main, nix builds the rest (keys, mesh grant, zfs
quota, dns). one object. git log answers who has access, who granted it,
when, and why. if that sounds slow, good. the friction is the curriculum.

web apps (mattermost etc) still need their own logins. git can't auth a
browser. that's fine. dex later if it gets annoying. not our problem today.

we removed the docs folder
--------------------------

sorry.

a lot of people open a repo, paste the whole docs tree into an ai, and ship
something they cannot explain when it breaks at 2am. the model will happily
hallucinate a runbook. you still will not know how the server works.

so there is no polished SETUP.md to launder into a chat window. the
configuration is the documentation. read the nix. read the commits. if you
cannot say what tank/users is for without searching, you are not ready to
run this box.

how to learn (actually)
-----------------------

1. read hosts/mothership/ then modules/ top to bottom. no skipping.
2. nix develop · nix flake check · nix eval the options until the graph
   is in your head (hostname, mesh ip, who imports what).
3. break a throwaway vm or a spare disk before you touch production metal.
4. when something fails, read the unit journal and the nixos option — not
   a summary of a summary of a blog post.
5. only after that: ask a model specific questions about one file you
   already opened. if you cannot point at the line, you are not asking a
   real question.

the admin-toil number is the only metric that decides whether this
survives. if operating it needs a wiki, we already lost.

if you know you know. if you don't, start at flake.nix and walk the
imports. that is the whole invitation.
